      package Recursion; public class App { public static void main(String[] args) { System.out.println(recursiveLinearSearch(new int [] {4,2,1,5,9,24,12}, 1, 24)); } public static void reduceByOne(int n) { if(n >= 0) { System.out.println("Completed call: " + n); reduceByOne(n-1); } // System.out.println("Completed call: " + n); } public static int recursiveLinearSearch(int [] a, int i, int x) { // a is the array, i starting point, x is value we are searching for in given array a if(i > a.length -1) { //if evaluates to true, x was not found return -1; } else if(a[i] == x) { return i; } else { System.out.println("It is not in index at: " + i); return recursiveLinearSearch(a, i+1, x); } } }
